summary.para: Start a loop of a specified step type. Each Step added between calling StartLoop and StopLoop is added to the loop.
If no steps will be added to the loop, all parameters should be set.
In Active mode: iterations, passed, failed and endingIndex will be set be set based on steps in the loop.
In Import mode: iterations, passed, failed and endingIndex must be set.
Valid step types are: SequenceCall, NumericLimitStep, StringValueStep, PassFailStep, CallExeStep, MessagePopupStep and GenericStep

member.param: Name of the loop. All steps in the loop must have same name.
Number of iterations contained in the loop. In Active mode will be set to the amount of steps the loop contains.
Index of the last loop iteration.
member.exception: Is thrown when T is invalid.
member.returns: The summary step of the loop. If StartLoop has already been called, returns null.
